node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jade Roper Tolbert on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text: Two years ago, our sweet Brooksy came into this world with a fury. A 70 minute labor brought me to my knees in our closet and there he was born! I’ve learned so much from this sweet, brave, keen boy. He is incredibly special and I feel he’s in this world to do amazing things. Happy Birthday, Brooksy! I’ll probably dedicate a million posts to you today because I’m so proud, and I’m so lucky I get to love you unconditionally! I can’t wait to celebrate you today, my beautiful babe!

node.text: Let’s talk about postpartum hair loss, it’s a real thing! I experienced it after all 3 of my babies, and 50% of women have significant hair loss or thinning postpartum. Swipe to see my bald patches. So why don’t people talk about it more? For me it was horrifying to watch how much hair I was losing every single day, so I went on the search to find a product that would stop the hair loss and also help me support new, healthy regrowth. @nutrafol is science backed and naturally targets several root issues of why we lose hair postpartum. I’ve been taking it for 3 months now, and my excessive shedding and hair loss has stopped and I can see so much regrowth, especially at my hairline. So come join me on this hair growth journey. Check out my stories and you’ll get $50 off your first 3 months of subscription! Seriously ladies you have to give this a try! Set yourself up for consistency, and ultimately improve your hair growth with @nutrafol!

node.text: Reed turned 8 months yesterday!! It’s feeling too real how fast this year is going, and I could definitely cry about it! Haha. 😂😭😭 This past month you’ve been army crawling all over the whole house and pulling yourself up on all the furniture so you can get a better look around your world, and also to see what your brother and sister are up to! You adore them and they  adore you! You’re saying Dada first just like Emmy and Brooks, but we all know I’m your number one. 😉😉 Love you, Reed!!

node.text:
Yesterday was my first skin treatment in years! I’ve been wanting to make my skin care more of a priority lately, so I am very excited to partner with @lumenis.aesthetic.us to show their newest treatments SmoothGlo and BeautifulEyes!  They are minimally invasive and only take about 15-20 minutes for each treatment. Swipe over to see a sneak peek of the machine! I had my first treatment yesterday and already notice a smoother complexion, my makeup went on so silky today. This photo is from this morning, just a day after my first treatments. I can’t wait to go back for the rest of my treatments and to show you my skin’s progress! What are you skin goals this year? #SmoothGlo #BeautifulEyesbyLumenis #LumenisPartner

node.text: This age is one of my favorites! Oh how I love him so! Reed is going to be getting into everything in no time, he’s pulling himself up onto furniture and interested in everything Emmy and Brooks are playing with when near. His smile lights up the room and those sweet eyes melt my whole heart! He is a mama’s boy through and through and we love watching his personality start to show itself more. 😊🥰
